===Film===
*''[[The Secret Life: Jeffrey Dahmer]]'' was released in 1993 and stars [[Carl Crew]] as Dahmer.<ref>[[IMDbTitle:0244782|''Jeffrey Dahmer: The Secret Life'']] at imdb.com</ref>
*The biographical film ''[[Dahmer (film)|Dahmer]]'' was released in 2002. It stars [[Jeremy Renner]] in the title role and co-stars [[Bruce Davison]] as Dahmer's father, Lionel.<ref>''Dahmer'' opened in theaters on June 21, 2002. [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0285728/releaseinfo ''Dahmer'' (2002)&nbsp;– Release Info]&nbsp;– IMDb. The DVD was released on October 27.[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0285728/dvd ''Dahmer'' (2002)]&nbsp;– IMDb</ref>
*''[[Raising Jeffrey Dahmer]]'' was released in 2006. Revolving around the reactions of Dahmer's parents following his arrest in 1991, it stars Rusty Sneary as Dahmer and co-stars Scott Cordes as Lionel.
*In 2012, an independent documentary, ''[[The Jeffrey Dahmer Files]]'', premiered at the [[South by Southwest]] festival. It features interviews with Dahmer's former neighbor, Pamela Bass, as well as Detective Patrick Kennedy, and the city [[medical examiner]] Jeffrey Jentzen.<ref>[https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/movies/2012/03/sxsw2012-lives-touched-by-dahmer-in-jeff.html "'Jeff' explores Dahmer's effect on Milwaukee"] ''Los Angeles Times''. March 10, 2012.</ref>
*The [[Marc Meyers]]-directed film, [[My Friend Dahmer (film)|''My Friend Dahmer'']], premiered at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]] on April 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/my-friend-dahmer-review-ross-lynch-1202401672/ |title= Tribeca Film Review: 'My Friend Dahmer' |first= Owen |last= Gleiberman |authorlink=Owen Gleiberman |date= April 27, 2017 |website= Variety.com |publisher= Variety Media, LLC |access-date= June 21, 2017}}</ref> Based on [[My Friend Dahmer|the graphic novel]] by [[Derf|John Backderf]], the film stars [[Ross Lynch]] as Dahmer and chronicles his high school years and the events leading up to his first murder.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Collis |first1=Clark |title=Ross Lynch Starring Serial Killer Film My Friend Dahmer to be Released This Fall|url=https://ew.com/movies/2017/05/15/ross-lynch-my-friend-dahmer-release-date/|date=May 15, 2017|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]|location=New York City}}</ref>

